{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'First}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

<code>X'{{Ada/attribute|First}}</code>, where <code>X</code> is any [[ada Programming/Types|scalar type]] (for example integer, enumerated, real), is an [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] that represents the first value (lower bound) in the range of type <code>X</code>. The value returned is of type <code>X</code>.

Note that the Ada attribute <code>X'{{Ada/attribute|Pos}}(0)</code> is not necessarily equivalent to <code>X'First</code>. The underlying position numbers of type <code>X</code> may follow an unusual convention.

== Example ==

 {{Ada/kw|type}} My_Enum {{Ada/kw|is}} (Enum1, Enum2, Enum3);
 {{Ada/kw|type}} My_Int  {{Ada/kw|is}} {{Ada/kw|range}} -1 .. 5;
 ... 
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'First = Enum1);   {{Template:Ada/comment|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Int'First  = -1);      {{Template:Ada/comment|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Int'First  =  0);      {{Template:Ada/comment|Wrong!}}

== See also ==

