{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Ceiling}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

X'Ceiling(Y) is an Ada [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] where X is any floating-point type and Y is any instance of that type. This attribute represents the smallest integer value that is greater than or equal to Y. 

== Example ==

 X : Float := 1.5;
 Y : Float := 1.0;
 Z : Float := 1.999;
 ... 
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Ceiling(X) = 2.0 );  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Ceiling(Y) = 1.0 );  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Ceiling(Z) = 1.0 );  {{Ada/--|Wrong}}

