[[Category:Ada Programming|Rounding]]

{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Unbiased_Rounding}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

X'Unbiased_Rounding(Y) is an Ada [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] where X is any floating-point type and Y is any instance of that type. This attribute represents the closest integer value to Y. If Y is exactly between two integer values (e.g. 1.5), then the result is the even value (e.g. 2.0). 

== Example ==

 X : Float := 1.5;
 Y : Float := 1.0;
 Z : Float := 1.999;
 ... 
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}}(Float'Unbiased_Rounding(X) = 2.0);  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}}(Float'Unbiased_Rounding(Y) = 1.0);  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}}(Float'Unbiased_Rounding(Z) = 2.0);  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}}(Float'Unbiased_Rounding(X) = 1.0);  {{Ada/--|Wrong}}
 ...
 X := 2.5;
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}}(Float'Unbiased_Rounding(X) = 2.0 );  {{Ada/--|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}}(Float'Unbiased_Rounding(X) = 3.0 );  {{Ada/--|Wrong}}

