{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Copy_Sign}}
__TOC__

 {{Ada/kw|function}} S'Copy_Sign (''Value'', ''Sign'' : ''T'')
   {{Ada/kw|return}} ''T''

== Description ==

S'Copy_Sign(X, Y) is an Ada [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] where S is any floating-point type, and X and Y are any instance of that type. This attribute represents the floating point value with the magnitude of X and the sign of Y.

If the resulting value is outside the range of S, a Constraint_Error exception is raised. 

== Example ==

 X : Float :=  1.5;
 Y : Float := -1.0;
 Z : Float :=  1.0;

 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Copy_Sign ( X, Y) = -1.5);   {{Template:Ada/comment|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Copy_Sign ( X, Z) =  1.5);   {{Template:Ada/comment|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Copy_Sign (-X, Z) =  1.5);   {{Template:Ada/comment|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (Float'Copy_Sign ( Y, Z) = -1.0);   {{Template:Ada/comment|Wrong}}

== See also ==

=== Wikibook ===

* [[Ada Programming]]
* [[Ada Programming/Attributes]]

=== Ada Reference Manual ===

