{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Digits}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

X'Digits is an Ada [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] where X is any floating point type or decimal fixed point type. This attribute represents the number of decimal digits in the mantissa of type X. 

== Example ==

 {{Ada/kw|type}} My_Float {{Ada/kw|is}} {{Ada/kw|digits}} 10 {{Ada/kw|range}} 0.0 .. 100.0;
 ... 
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Float'Digits = 10);  {{Ada/--|OK}}

== See also ==

=== Wikibook ===

* [[Ada Programming]]
* [[Ada Programming/Attributes]]

=== Ada Reference Manual ===

* {{Ada/RM2|13|3|Operational and Representation Attributes}}
* {{Ada/RMA1|K|Language-Defined Attributes}}


[[Category:Ada Programming|Digits]]

{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Width}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

X'Width is an Ada [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] where X is any discrete type. This attribute represents the number of characters it takes to represent the "longest" type value using the [[Ada Programming/Attributes/'Image|X'Image]] attribute.

== Example ==

 {{Ada/kw|type}} My_Enum {{Ada/kw|is}} (Big, Bigger, Biggest);
 ...
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Image (Biggest) = "BIGGEST" );
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Width = 7); 
 {{Ada/--|Width of "BIGGEST" is seven}}
 {{Ada/--|Width of "BIG" and "BIGGER" are irrelevant.}}

