{{Ada/Navigation|Attributes|'Value}}
__TOC__

== Description ==

The 'Value [[Ada Programming/Attributes|attribute]] is defined for any scalar type. This attribute is a function that parses the string and returns the corresponding type value, if it exists. Leading and trailing spaces are trimmed.

 {{Ada/kw|function}} S'Value (Arg: String) {{Ada/kw|return}} S'Base;

If the string does not correspond to any value of the type, then the Constraint_Error [[Ada Programming/Exceptions|exception]] is raised.

There are corresponding attributes for Wide_String and Wide_Wide_String.

Don't confuse this attribute with the [[Ada Programming/Attributes/'Val]] attribute.
== Example ==

 {{Ada/kw|type}} My_Enum {{Ada/kw|is}} (Enum1, Enum2, Enum3);

 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Value ("ENUM1")    = Enum1); {{Template:Ada/comment|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Value ("  ENUM1 ") = Enum1); {{Template:Ada/comment|OK}}
 {{Ada/pragma|Assert}} (My_Enum'Value ("ZOWIE!")   = Enum1); {{Template:Ada/comment|Wrong! Constraint_Error is raised}}

